Reasoning: The paper discusses the application of compressed sensing to wireless communication systems, which falls under the intersection of information theory (cs.IT) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). The paper also discusses sparse recovery algorithms and performance guarantees, which are topics in signal processing (cs.SI) and multimedia (cs.MM). Additionally, the paper provides tips and tricks for designing CS-based wireless communication systems, which could fall under machine learning (cs.LG) as it involves optimizing system performance.
